node.text:
US Rep. Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez took to the 2021 #MetGala with a bright red message for Americans: "Tax the Rich."⁠
⁠
"When we talk about supporting working families and when we talk about having a fair tax code, oftentimes this conversation is happening among working and middle-class people (on) the Senate floor," Ocasio-Cortez said. "I think it's time we bring all classes into the conversation."⁠
⁠
(📸: Kevin Mazur/MG21/Getty Images For The Met Museum/Vogue)

node.text:
FinanceBuzz will pay an individual $1,300 to watch 13 scary movies in October, in an effort to find out whether the size of a movie's budget impacts its scariness. They will monitor the person's heart rate during the films using Fitbit, the company said.⁠
⁠
The chosen participant is required to watch the following films: Saw, Amityville Horror, A Quiet Place, A Quiet Place Part 2, Candyman, Insidious, The Blair Witch Project, Sinister, Get Out, The Purge, Halloween (2018), Paranormal Activity and Annabelle.⁠
⁠
(📸: Blumhouse Productions/Miramax/Alamy)⁠

node.text:
Maia Chaka made history on Sunday by becoming the first Black woman to officiate an NFL game. "This historic moment to me is an honor and it's a privilege that I've been chosen to represent women and women of color in the most popular sport in America," said Chaka, who is a health and physical education teacher.⁠
⁠
(📸: Jim Dedmon/USA TODAY Sports)

node.text:
North Korea claims it successfully test-fired new long-range cruise missiles over the weekend, according to state-run media. Cruise missiles are propelled by jet engines. Much like an airplane, they stay closer to the ground, making them harder to detect.⁠
⁠
The photo above is from North Korean state-run newspaper Rodong Sinmun, showing what North Korean authorities say was a successful test launch on September 11 or 12.⁠
⁠
(📸: Rodong Sinmun)

⁠

227 people were killed defending the environment last year, according to a new report by Global Witness. That's a record.⁠
